[2
Date: 06 Nov 2000
From: M. Cosgriff <mcosgriff@hotmail.com>
Source: Australian Broadcast Corp., 6 Nov 2000 [edited
<http://www.abc.net.au/ra/newsdaily/s208908.htm>

France Prepares for Bonemeal Ban
--------------------------------------------
France is set to ban the use of bone meal and other animal parts in animal
feed amid growing fears over mad cow disease. Agriculture minister Jean
Glavany says the use of such animal feed has caused many problems. He says
banning the animal feed will make life simpler, even if it is not strictly
a question of food safety.
France has been thrown into panic in recent weeks, with some supermarkets
withdrawing their beef stocks after the news that meat from a herd
contaminated with mad cow disease, or BSE, was put on sale in supermarkets.
Some 84 BSE cases have been reported in France so far this year, and 164
since recording began in 1991. Hungary said it is banning French imports of
beef beginning tomorrow, while Russia says it will not accept beef from a
number of high-risk areas in the west of France.
